dines.name: Brunch Deluxe
dines.description: Luxurious platters of the freshest harvest, begin your day or end your weekend with the most dazzling of all brunches.

dines.name: Dinner and Dine
dines.description: Spend an evening dining on breathtaking and delicious trays from around the world. Straight from local and organic farms.

dines.name: Happy Hour Escape
dines.description: Let our happy hour take away your stress. Sit back, relax, and enjoy our most elegant cocktails.

dines.name: Dessert Delicacies
dines.description: Once you try one of our world famous desserts, you will never quit coming back.

comments.text: The brunch is incredible, much better than others in town.
comments.author: Elon Mixer

comments.text: The waffles are spectacular... so my wife ate all mine.
comments.author: Alicia Kazzi

comments.text: The egg dishes are all great, but they are absolutely best poached.
comments.author: Benjamin Morey

comments.text: Avoid Sundays; couldn't relax and play my flute with all the noisy kids.
comments.author: Elise Kanton

comments.text: This has been our favorite restaurant for over 7 years. It is an absolutely beautiful establishment. The hosts are very friendly and helpful. Don't forget to try out the Salmon and Locks.
comments.author: Bryant Posy

comments.text: There's nothing more fun than coming to dinner at Dinera and relaxing for hours.
comments.author: Michelle Ali

comments.text: I tried the world-class fillet mignon here on my last visit, and it was mind blowing.
comments.author: Rachel Soprano

comments.text: The restaurant was beautiful, but they are often reserved out for a few days.
comments.author: Kwame Britain

comments.text: Love the menu but they were out of menu items with grapefruit.
comments.author: Sadie Harris

comments.text: A wonderful place to try new foods and know it will taste great.
comments.author: Jordan Modelo

comments.text: The Frozen Pineapple is amazing, but it is strong so be careful!
comments.author: Christopher Wallace

comments.text: We had to leave about 2am to go back to the home because the party lasted too long!
comments.author: George Lucas

comments.text: The stars from the rooftop make it a great place for drinks!
comments.author: Diana Rosen

comments.text: Easy parking and a nice place to have a drink after work.
comments.author: Amy Gambino

comments.text: Perfect scenery and nice jazz music to sit back!
comments.author: Janessa Messey

comments.text: Just remember too much sugar will make you sleepy...
comments.author: Penny Delphi

comments.text: Excellent desserts to cleanse the palette after a nice meal.
comments.author: Jenna Maui

comments.text: What magnificent flourles chocolate cake!
comments.author: Martin Post

comments.text: The desserts are huge! We felt like we might not be able to walk out, in a good way.
comments.author: Anisha Brodst

comments.text: The photos don't do justice to the wonder of these desserts.
comments.author: Ashley Adrena
